%N A218421 Number of n X 3 binary arrays with every 0 a horizontal, vertical or antidiagonal neighbor to some 1.
%H A218421 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A218421/b218421.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..210</a>
%H A218421 <a href="/index/Rec#order_11">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (5,16,28,17,7,-3,3,-8,0,-1,1).
%F A218421 Empirical: a(n) = 5*a(n-1) +16*a(n-2) +28*a(n-3) +17*a(n-4) +7*a(n-5) -3*a(n-6) +3*a(n-7) -8*a(n-8) -a(n-10) +a(n-11).
%F A218421 From _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 15 2026: (Start)
%F A218421 The above empirical formula confirmed using the transfer matrix method.
%F A218421 G.f.: x*(1 + x)*(5 + 19*x + 13*x^2 + 3*x^3 - 4*x^4 + 4*x^5 - 9*x^6 + x^7 - x^8 + x^9)/((1 + x + x^2 - x^3)*(1 - 6*x - 11*x^2 - 10*x^3 - 2*x^4 - 6*x^5 + x^6 + x^8)). (End)
%e A218421 Some solutions for n=3:
